Yes. Yes. And horses. And cattle. And cattle. That's the grandfather but not - not the uncles, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8731373 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9518286\charrsid5125818 
Could you tell me about the meals at that time, can you tell me about a typical days meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8202071 DC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9518286\charrsid5125818 
Well, porridge and milk in the morning. Scones. Tea. Or scones and milk. Before I got to - go to school. Yes. Dinner, potatoes and fish. And plenty of milk. Supper again, potatoes sometimes or - porridge. There was no such a thing as meat. Only an }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3034638\charrsid5125818 occasional}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9518286\charrsid5125818  - once in a blue moon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8731373 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9518286\charrsid5125818 Not even rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8202071 DC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9518286\charrsid5125818 No, not - not in Barra. No. No.
