\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8202071 DC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9518286\charrsid5125818 
Well shooting them that's all. That's all. But Neil, up there, he used to get - cormorants, young cormorants up there. And they're -
 they're a lovely dish. When they're - when they're fried, cooked first and then - put them on the frying pan. Oh they're lovely dishes, lovely. I like them myself. I get one occasionally from - from man that's down there, he used to go up to Mingulay at 
t
he time when they were coming down from their nests. Aye. And - and the stable food at that time - it was - it was - it was - the best you could get here - get today, if I could get the food that I had in my young days I would - I would live for another h
undred years. You know that?
