\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9518286\charrsid5125818  that came here - sixteen shillings a ton. Guess what it is today? Fourteen shillings a ton. Down there. There you are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8731373 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9518286\charrsid5125818 Did you buy new clothes from a shop or were they made in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8202071 DC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9518286\charrsid5125818 Oh it was bought - some - most of it. Oh yes.
 Yes, because - the first suit that I had was a sailor suit, which was taken from the - the east coast, bought at the east coast anyway, at the time they were going for the fishing, they would have - they had a suit - first suit that I ever had - a sailor
 suit, with a whistle attached to it. Yes. That was - be around about - nine or ten years old then. Yes. And after that - they was buying the made - ready made suits you see in - in the shops. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8731373 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9518286\charrsid5125818 Who would mend them, would your mother or your father mend the clothes?
