Well - unfortunately, yes, I took - to - to be - to be a Tory. I'll tell you the honest truth. Yes. And I still - kept it going, Tory party, see? Although it was the Liberal party that - sanctioned this lot as regards the isl
and of Vatersay. I - was a Tory, voting a Tory. Right to this year. Yes, this last election. But - I'm dead against it now. Yes. Since this man went in - I don't like it. No. He - he's letting Scotland down. Scotland's a disgrace to Britain, as regards un
e
mployment, everything else. It's a dmaned shame. I don't care if you're an Englishman but - it's - I don't care for - see? See? Because - everything that's in the country, look at the - look at the - the C.S. - U.C.S. Upper Clyde - Shipbuilding, look at -
 
look at the mess that they made of that. It's a damned shame Why - if that firm wasn't paying, why in the name of heavens were no management attached to it that would - could see - after they got their twenty million, that they could see and manage to - t
o
 carry the thing through in a proper manner. That would pay itself. I don't - I don't agree with that at all. I do not. And another thing - the day that Scotland - that England, Great - U.K. goes into the Common Market, Scotland's her own - island. Yes. I
'll tell you that straight. And you'll live more - longer than me. And you'll see it. Oh no.
